Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
displayBufTree(25.10)                                    displayBufTree(25.10)

Name
       displayBufTree  -  Displays a buffer tree associated with the specified
       net

Syntax
        displayBufTree

       [-help]

       -net <netName>

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       Displays a buffer tree associated with the specified net.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each displayBufTree parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man displayBufTree.

       -net <netName>
              Specifies  the name of the net for which you want to display the
              buffer tree.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the text file containing buffer locations.

Example
              * The following command highlights instances and  wires  in  the
                buffer  tree  associated with the net reset in the design dis-
                play area:

                displayBufTree -net reset

                displayBufTree -outfile reset_buftree

